2 SENATE BILL 558
1 BY adding to
2 Article – Natural Resources
3 Section 4–1020.1
4 Annotated Code of Maryland
5 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
6 BY adding to
7 Article – Economic Development
8 Section 10–526.1 and 10–526.2
9 Annotated Code of Maryland
10 (2024 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
11 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
12 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
13 Article – Natural Resources
14 4–1020.1.
15 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “PROGRAM” MEANS THE CHESAPEAKE BAY
16 ENHANCEMENT PROGRAM.
17 (B) THERE IS A CHESAPEAKE BAY ENHANCEMENT PROGRAM IN THE
18 DEPARTMENT.
19 (C) THE PURPOSE OF THE PROGRAM IS TO PROVIDE FUNDING FOR OYSTER
20 PROPAGATION AND REPLENISHMENT PROJECTS THAT MITIGATE THE EFFECTS ON
21 THE STATE’S OYSTER POPULATION OF TRANSPORTATION PROJECTS THAT
22 MAINTAIN OR EXPAND THE HELEN DELICH BENTLEY PORT OF BALTIMORE,
23 INCLUDING:
24 (1) DREDGING;
25 (2) THE CONSTRUCTION OR MAINTENANCE OF:
26 (I) PIERS;
27 (II) BRIDGES; OR
28 (III) SHIPPING CHANNELS; AND
29 (3) CONSTRUCTION AT THE HELEN DELICH BENTLEY PORT OF
30 BALTIMORE OF TRANSPORTATION PROJECTS ON THE STATE’S OYSTER
31 POPULATION.

SENATE BILL 558 3
1 (D) FOR FISCAL YEAR 2028 AND EACH FISCAL YEAR THEREAFTER, THE
2 GOVERNOR SHALL INCLUDE IN THE ANNUAL BUDGET BILL AN APPROPRIATION OF
3 $2,000,000 $2,250,000 TO THE PROGRAM FROM THE TRANSPORTATION TRUST
4 FUND UNDER § 3–216 OF THE TRANSPORTATION ARTICLE.
5 (E) (1) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ADMINISTER THE FUNDS
6 APPROPRIATED UNDER SUBSECTION (D) OF THIS SECTION.
7 (2) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ALLOCATE THE FUNDS APPROPRIATED
8 UNDER SUBSECTION (D) OF THIS SECTION USE FUNDING UNDER THE PROGRAM TO
9 SUPPORT OYSTER PROPAGATION AND REPLENISHMENT AND PROGRAM
10 MANAGEMENT.
11 (3) NOTWITHSTANDING PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION, THE
12 DEPARTMENT SHALL ALLOCATE AT LEAST $1,500,000 OF THE FUNDS
13 APPROPRIATED UNDER SUBSECTION (D) OF THIS SECTION FOR OYSTER
14 PROPAGATION AND REPLENISHMENT PROJECTS.
15 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That the Laws of Maryland read
16 as follows:
17 Article – Economic Development
18 10–526.1.
19 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “FUND” MEANS THE MARYLAND SEAFOOD INDUSTRY
20 FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE FUND.
21 (B) THERE IS A MARYLAND SEAFOOD INDUSTRY FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE
22 FUND.
23 (C) THE PURPOSE OF THE FUND IS TO PROVIDE FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE,
24 INCLUDING LOANS, TO COMMERCIAL WATERMEN AND SMALL BUSINESSES IN THE
25 SEAFOOD INDUSTRY.
26 (D) THE CORPORATION SHALL ADMINISTER THE FUND.
27 (E) (1) THE FUND IS A SPECIAL, NONLAPSING FUND THAT IS NOT
28 SUBJECT TO § 7–302 OF THE STATE FINANCE AND PROCUREMENT ARTICLE.
29 (2) THE STATE TREASURER SHALL HOLD THE FUND SEPARATELY,
30 AND THE COMPTROLLER SHALL ACCOUNT FOR THE FUND.

4 SENATE BILL 558
1 (F) THE FUND CONSISTS OF:
2 (1) MONEY APPROPRIATED IN THE STATE BUDGET TO THE FUND;
3 (2) FEES AND LOAN REPAYMENTS, INCLUDING INTEREST, LOAN
4 PRINCIPAL REPAYMENTS RELATED TO THE FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE UNDER THIS
5 SECTION;
6 (3) MONEY MADE AVAILABLE FROM THE FEDERAL, STATE, OR LOCAL
7 GOVERNMENT; AND
8 (4) ANY OTHER MONEY FROM ANY OTHER SOURCE ACCEPTED FOR
9 THE BENEFIT OF THE FUND.
10 (G) (F) THE FUND MAY BE USED ONLY FOR:
11 (1) FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE, INCLUDING LOANS; AND
12 (2) THE COSTS OF THE CORPORATION TO ADMINISTER THIS SECTION.
13 (H) THE STATE TREASURER SHALL INVEST THE MONEY OF THE FUND IN
14 THE SAME MANNER AS OTHER STATE MONEY MAY BE INVESTED.
15 (I) EXPENDITURES FROM THE FUND MAY BE MADE ONLY IN ACCORDANCE
16 WITH THE STATE BUDGET.
17 (J) (G) FOR FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE, INCLUDING LOANS, PROVIDED
18 UNDER THIS SECTION, THE CORPORATION SHALL DETERMINE THE FOLLOWING:
19 (1) THE APPLICATION AND AWARD PROCESS;
20 (2) ELIGIBILITY CRITERIA;
21 (3) THE AMOUNT OF THE FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE, INCLUDING LOANS,
22 FOR EACH APPLICANT;
23 (4) THE TERMS AND CONDITIONS OF FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE,
24 INCLUDING LOANS;
25 (5) THE AMOUNT OF LOAN FORGIVENESS THAT THE CORPORATION
26 MAY PROVIDE FOR LOAN REPAYMENT PERFORMANCE; AND

SENATE BILL 558 5
1 (6) ANY OTHER PROVISIONS NECESSARY TO CARRY OUT THIS
2 SECTION.
3 10–526.2.
4 (A) (1) IF A BORROWER WHO HOLDS A TIDAL FISH LICENSE UNDER §
5 4–701 OF THE NATURAL RESOURCES ARTICLE IS DELINQUENT IN THE REPAYMENT
6 OF A LOAN UNDER THIS SUBTITLE, THE CORPORATION SHALL NOTIFY THE
7 DEPARTMENT OF NATURAL RESOURCES.
8 (2) IF A BORROWER UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION
9 BECOMES COMPLIANT WITH THE REPAYMENT OF A LOAN UNDER THIS SUBTITLE,
10 THE CORPORATION SHALL NOTIFY THE DEPARTMENT OF NATURAL RESOURCES.
11 (B) NOTWITHSTANDING § 4–701 OF THE NATURAL RESOURCES ARTICLE,
12 AFTER RECEIVING A NOTIFICATION UNDER SUBSECTION (A)(1) OF THIS SECTION
13 AND UNTIL RECEIVING A NOTIFICATION UNDER SUBSECTION (A)(2) OF THIS
14 SECTION, THE DEPARTMENT OF NATURAL RESOURCES MAY NOT APPROVE A
15 TRANSFER OF THE TIDAL FISH LICENSE OR AUTHORIZATION.
16 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That:
17 (1) the Maryland Agricultural and Resource–Based Industry Development
18 Corporation may transfer up to $337,500 each from the Oyster Shucking House Loan
19 Program and the Watermen’s Microloan Program to the Maryland Seafood Industry
20 Financial Assistance Fund established under Section 2 of this Act to provide additional
21 financial assistance to commercial watermen and small businesses in the seafood industry;
22 and
23 (2) the Maryland Agricultural and Resource–Based Industry Development
24 Corporation shall repay any funds transferred from the Oyster Shucking House Loan
25 Program or the Watermen’s Microloan Program to the Maryland Seafood Industry
26 Financial Assistance Fund established under Section 2 of this Act on or before June 30,
27 2028.
28 SECTION 3. 4. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That Section 2 Sections 2 and 3
29 of this Act shall take effect July 1, 2026.
30 SECTION 2. 4. 5. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That, except as provided in
31 Section 3 4 of this Act, this Act shall take effect October 1, 2026.

